**B. `compute_scores_kernel`** — verbatim from parent. Guard `if (seq_len <= 2048) return;` already present. Writes scores/indices into `scores_buf`/`indices_buf` at `[b*N + p*64 + t]`. Used by all of TIER-M, L2, L.

**C. `block_topk_kernel<256, 24>`** — verbatim from parent. Guard `if (L <= 2048 || L > L_MED_MAX) return;`. Handles TIER-M.

**D. NEW `block_topk_kernel_large<512, 24>`** — handles TIER-L2. Structure copied from `block_topk_kernel`, only parameters change:
```cpp
